views.text: Peacegate Negotiation can be used to invite a person for online negotiation, either to resolve a dispute or to make a deal. You can enter the Whatsapp number or email of the person with whom you would like to negotiate and an invitation will be issued to the other side by email and notification. On the other side accepting your request, you will receive an email and notification and you can commence the negotiation online. If the other side refuse to negotiate, that will also be intimated to you by email and notification.

views.text: The entire conversation in the chat room gets auto-deleted on exiting the chat room, maintaining complete confidentiality/privacy of the process. If the other person refuses to communicate, or if the negotiation fails, you can end negotiation and can opt to refer the dispute for mediation, if you want. As parties, both of you can also bring in additional parties whom you think would be essential for the negotiation and in the same manner remove the additional parties. All the best for your negotiation!
